clubText: Bring Change to Mind's High School Program gives teens a platform to share their voices and raise awareness around mental health. Our goal is to empower students to educate one another and to foster a culture of peer support about mental health at FHS.  The club organizes thematic monthly meetings or community outreach, maintains the Wellness Room in Guidance, and plans and staffs the student-run event, Hope for Happiness, which occurs every May in the Nickel Plate District.
